│ This document outlines the exhaustive, multi-phase plan to transition the Local Brand e-commerce platform from a prototype to a       │
│ production-ready, Vercel-deployed application. It covers all necessary database updates, backend hardening, frontend completion, and  │
│ deployment configurations.                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│ Phase 1: Foundation & Security Hardening (Backend First)                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│ Objective: Secure the application, ensure data integrity, and implement robust validation.                                            │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│  1. Strict Request Validation (Zod Integration)                                                                                       │
│      * Action: Install zod and create schema definitions for all API inputs and Server Actions.                                       │
│      * Targets: src/app/api/** and src/app/actions/**.                                                                                │
│      * Details: Validate email formats, password strength, required fields, and strictly type request bodies before touching the      │
│        database.                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│  2. Authentication & Authorization Overhaul                                                                                           │
│      * Action: Remove the hardcoded DEBUG_BYPASS_KEY from src/lib/auth.ts.                                                            │
│      * Action: Enhance src/middleware.ts or implement a dedicated RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) utility to strictly protect routes │
│        based on role (BUYER, SELLER, ADMIN).                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│  3. Database Atomicity (Prisma Transactions)                                                                                          │
│      * Action: Refactor critical operations to use prisma.$transaction.                                                               │
│      * Targets: src/app/api/checkout/split/route.ts and src/app/actions/orders.ts.                                                    │
│      * Details: Ensure that stock deductions, order creation, and loyalty point updates happen atomically. If one fails, everything   │
│        rolls back.                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│  4. Schema Adjustments (Prisma)                                                                                                       │
│      * Action: Update prisma/schema.prisma.                                                                                           │
│      * Changes:                                                                                                                       │
│          * Add images (String[]) to the Review model to support user photo uploads.                                                   │
│          * Add explicit platform fee tracking (e.g., commissionAmount) per OrderItem or Order to support split payouts.               │
│          * Add structured bank details fields to the SellerProfile model.                                                             │
│          * Consider adding an isLocal or originCity field to Product for the "Egyptian-made" filtering requirement.                   │
